Peel and slice your @onion{1} in half lengthways through the root. Turn the onion widthways and slice it very, very thinly into half moon shapes. Peel and finely chop the @garlic{2%cloves}. Chop the @new potatoes{1} in half. Chop the @cherry tomatoes{1%punnet} in half and very, very finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{3%sprigs}.

> About 30 minutes total cooking time. We love the instant gratification of food. The best things in life often take a long time to create, but a great recipe is the perfect antidote to long term graft. One minute it's a picture and a few lines of text on a recipe card, 30 minutes later it's sitting on a plate in front of you and 35 minutes later it's gone!

Add @olive oil{1%tbsp} to a #pan on medium heat. Add the onion and garlic with @salt{1/4%tsp} and gently cook for ~{10%minutes}. We don't want to colour the onions so if they begin to brown off then add @water{1%tbsp} and turn the heat down a little bit. Bear in mind that after 10 mins you'll be adding the cherry tomatoes.

Meanwhile, on medium-high heat, boil a #medium-sized pot{} of water big enough for your new potatoes with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Boil the new potatoes for around ~{12-15%minutes}. To test them for 'done-ness' stick a #knife in them: if it goes through easily and the potato drops off the knife then they are ready. When they are cooked drain them and keep to the side.

When the onions and garlic have been cooking for 10 mins, add the cherry tomatoes to the pan together with the @lilliput capers{1%tbsp} and keep cooking for another ~{10%minutes}. The mixture should start to bubble and the tomatoes will soften up.

Heat @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is very hot sprinkle a little @salt{} on both sides of the @sea bass fillets{2} and lay it gently in the pan skin side down. Cook it for ~{3%minutes} on the skin side without touching it. Now gently turn it over and cook for another ~{2%minutes}, before removing from the heat.

Add the @white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}(if you have some) to the cherry tomato mixture. Stir and cook for ~{3%minutes} before removing from the heat. Stir through 2 tbsps of the parsley.

Serve everything together with a sprinkle of parsley on top and get stuck in!